00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Science has a clearer story about photolithography chips than social media does.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:10,400
Photolithography chips are the backbone of modern electronics, etching intricate patterns onto silicon wafers.

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:17,600
This process allows billions of tiny transistors to fit in a tiny space, making devices smaller and faster.

4
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:23,200
Scientists are constantly pushing the limits, exploring new materials and techniques to improve efficiency.

5
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:28,400
Understanding photolithography is key to grasping how our world is digitized and interconnected.

